{
  "text": "In healthy adult human skin, most T RM cells are CD103 -CD4 + and reside in the dermis. While CD103 + T RM , both CD4 + and CD8 + , are more frequent in the epidermis, recirculating T cells are the minority among both CD4 + and CD8 + T-cell populations in skin [CITATION_1] . The resident T-cell populations in human skin thus differ in their migration compartments and functional capacities.",
  "correct_citation": {
